      <story-so-far>
        <reasoning>This passage primarily advances Kira's recovery and daily routines: she slept (~9 hours), Buddy confirmed stable vitals, Holloway ran the daily wellness protocol, and Remedy performed a wound reassessment that updated the care timeline (daily care 4–5 more days, then alternate days; full healing ~two weeks). It also introduces a new logistics friction: Holloway requires a formal dietary assessment (≈4 hours) before approving human-compatible food, and Kira agrees to begin it. I consolidated earlier, more granular intake/orientation and the variety of plant personalities into a single entry about Holloway/Remedy/Buddy to keep the running summary compact and focused on what matters going forward (medical status, resources, and bureaucratic obstacles). I updated the previous recovery estimate (about one week) to the new estimate (maybe two weeks) and kept only supply/ship/AI facts that remain relevant.</reasoning>
        <summary>
          - Shuttle experienced FTL drop-out and crash; Jensen and Reed died; Kira Voss survived with head bleeding, bruised ribs, and wounded right leg. Primary ship AI SAM is offline; emergency neural-link AI 'Buddy' (childlike persona) is active.
          - Shuttle hull breached; planet has breathable atmosphere and freshwater source ~800 m southwest. Shuttle comms, propulsion, and distress beacon damaged; life support on emergency reserves (~48 hours). Surviving supplies include sealed water, ~one week of rations, basic med supplies, tools, tarp, and a locked temperature-controlled 'Biological Samples' container.
          - Kira encountered a mobile plant collective (Holloway) — a scout sphere plus coordinated vine/fruiting-plant network — that speaks human Standard, performed intake and workplace-safety orientation, and offered itself as emergency contact; she was assigned temporary quarters and accompanied by a Scout.
          - Holloway required documented consents for treatments; a humanoid salvage/medic robot, Remedy, examined Kira's leg and synthesized antibacterial, anti-inflammatory, and analgesic compounds from mushrooms and fungal networks to treat an active bacterial colonization.
          - Remedy's initial treatment halted bacterial colonization, stabilized the wound, and Kira rested; Remedy has been producing antibacterial mushrooms daily for ongoing care.
          - Kira woke after ~9 hours sleep; Buddy reported stable vitals. She completed Holloway's daily wellness check (self-rated 7/10, no new symptoms).
          - Remedy performed a daily wound assessment: bandage removed, wound ~70% closed, tissue regeneration progressing, bacterial colonization halted; fresh antibacterial gel and bandage applied. Remedy recommends daily wound care for another 4–5 days, then every other day; estimated full healing ≈ two weeks.
          - Kira is hungry but Holloway requires a formal dietary assessment and approval for human-compatible food (standard protocol ~4 hours); Kira consented to begin the process.
          - Kira is adapting to Holloway/Remedy/Buddy's bureaucratic care routines and forming attachments to the plant collective while rescue remains uncertain.
        </summary>
